attracc.attraccr: Standard ARC/INFO attribute accuracy in Feature Attribute Tables like AREA, PERIMETER, etc. depend on horizontal positional accuracy. All the additional attributes are character type.

qattracc.attracce: All the Attributes besides standard ARC/INFO are character type. Standard verification of attributes reliability has been done by ARC/INFO EDITPLOT program to find out polygons without assigned character value or with more than one value.

dataqual.logic: Since the data set is the ARC/INFO coverage topological consistency are supported. Fuzzy tolerance has been maintained the same through all processing steps. Based on fuzzy tolerance value all undershoots and overshoots were detected and deleted. A comparison between color plot and original paper map was carried out by visual comparison. Color plots in 1:5,000,000 scale were superimposed on every of correspondent original map sheets. All detected errors in attributes were corrected.
dataqual.complete: Several geological age subdivisions on the original (UNESCO) 1:5,000,000 geologic maps were combined into a single unit. As of May, 2000, generalizations of the original geologic map (UNESCO) were carried out: 1. All the Cretaceous units were combined into one. 2. All the Precambrian subdivisions were combined into one. Boundaries are correct as of July, 1997.

horizpa.horizpar: 1. Original geological maps are of 500 m. maximum accuracy (0.1 mm on paper map of 1:5,000,000 scale). 2. Scanned images were of 200 dot/inch resolution (0.12 mm on paper). That is why fuzzy tolerance for CLEAN program in ARC/INFO was set to 500 m. Average positional accuracy can be evaluated as 1000 m (twice of fuzzy tolerance).
